the california student aid commission ( csac ) will notify students if they are selected to receive a middle class scholarship (mcs). the mcs will be awarded upon verifying eligibility requirements. students may receive the mcs award for up to 4 years, depending on education level when awarded. awards are expected to post in mid janaury for students attending during fall 2022 and spring 2023. visit the csac middle class scholarship web page for more information. email: fao@sjsu.edu _________________________ phone: 408-283-7500 ext 4 monday to friday 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. _________________________ live chat tuesday to friday 12:00 p.m. to 4:00 p.m. __________________________ virtual appointments friday from 10:00 a.m - 3:00 p.m. _________________________ in-person appointments monday to thursday 8:15 a.m. to 4:45 p.m. friday 9:00 a.m. to 4:30 p.m. __________________________ student services center (ssc) 9 street & san fernando (on 1 floor of north parking garage) financial aid and scholarship office san jos√© state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0036 